A Senatorial aspirant of the All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA), during 2019 general elections, Dr. Dele Ngargbu, has decamped to the All Progressives Congress (APC). The aspirant made his decision known to our correspondent in Keffi, Nasarawa State, yesterday. Ngargbu contested to represent Nasarawa West Senatorial zone known as Keffi zone of Nasarawa State. The aspirant, who is an academic doctor of medical geology cum politician hails from Kokona Local Government Area of the State. He had contested one political office or the other in the past which includes to represent his people in the national assembly of both the Green and the Red chambers respectively, but he lost. He said the quest to serve Nigeria is the only motivation for his defectionwhy from APGA for APC. “My goal in joining the APC is to lay intellect and my little exposure in life to spray an exposure towards the betterment of service delivery to the people of Nasarawa State.” “I will continue to remain my drive in politics as I keep saying that Nigeria deserve a better deal and to make it happen one need opportunities to prove such and where opportunity is calling you don’t say no” “The focus for every politician should be his society. So, everybody who is aspiring to contribute his or her qauta to national development most have the largeness of heart to be able to go beyond platforms and head straight to society and make the necessary contributions” “We have not quarrelled  with anybody. In fact, I have gone round to inform those who are strong allies of mine in politics be them in PDP, APC or APGA that I have a new drive and there is a need for a new chapter in Nasarawa State which is collectivism for the betterment of our state and Nigeria as a whole” he said.